# PART 12: GRAPH PROBLEMS — GOOGLE FAVORITES

---

## 12.1 Clone Graph (LeetCode 133)

```java
public Node cloneGraph(Node node) {
    if (node == null) return null;
    Map<Node, Node> map = new HashMap<>();
    return dfsClone(node, map);
}

private Node dfsClone(Node node, Map<Node, Node> map) {
    if (map.containsKey(node)) return map.get(node);
    Node clone = new Node(node.val);
    map.put(node, clone);
    for (Node neighbor : node.neighbors) {
        clone.neighbors.add(dfsClone(neighbor, map));
    }
    return clone;
}
```

## 12.2 Word Ladder (BFS shortest transformation)

```
  "hit" → "hot" → "dot" → "dog" → "cog"   (4 transformations)
  Change one letter at a time, each intermediate word must be valid.
```

```java
public int ladderLength(String beginWord, String endWord, List<String> wordList) {
    Set<String> wordSet = new HashSet<>(wordList);
    if (!wordSet.contains(endWord)) return 0;

    Queue<String> queue = new LinkedList<>();
    queue.offer(beginWord);
    int level = 1;

    while (!queue.isEmpty()) {
        int size = queue.size();
        for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
            char[] word = queue.poll().toCharArray();

            for (int j = 0; j < word.length; j++) {
                char original = word[j];
                for (char c = 'a'; c <= 'z'; c++) {
                    word[j] = c;
                    String newWord = new String(word);
                    if (newWord.equals(endWord)) return level + 1;
                    if (wordSet.contains(newWord)) {
                        queue.offer(newWord);
                        wordSet.remove(newWord);
                    }
                }
                word[j] = original;
            }
        }
        level++;
    }
    return 0;
}
```

## 12.3 Course Schedule (Cycle Detection in Directed Graph)

```java
// Can you finish all courses? (No cycles in prerequisite graph)
public boolean canFinish(int numCourses, int[][] prerequisites) {
    // Use topological sort — if we can sort all courses, no cycle exists
    int[] result = topologicalSort(numCourses, prerequisites);
    return result.length == numCourses;
}
```

